<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 4:28PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Lewis and
Clark County through 500 PM MDT...
At 428 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Augusta, or 28 miles west of Cascade, moving northeast
at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Augusta, Bean Lake and Bowmans Corner.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
